The paper deals with the problem of selecting a set of views to be materialized in a Semantic Web database, which involves optimizing query processing, view storage, and view maintenance costs. This problem is closely related to database management and optimization, which falls under the category of cs.DB. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel RDF query reformulation algorithm, which involves reasoning and inference, and can be categorized under cs.AI. The paper also discusses the scalability of the proposed algorithms, which can be related to machine learning and optimization, falling under cs.LG. Furthermore, the paper deals with query processing and information retrieval, which can be categorized under cs.IR. Finally, the paper proposes new algorithms for recommending view sets, which can be related to software engineering and design, falling under cs.SE.
